/tsconfig.json                     - TypeScript configuration
/.gitignore                        - Git ignore rules
/src/app.ts                        - Express app setup and middleware
/src/server.ts                     - Server entry point
/src/types.ts                      - Type definitions (User, Post, Comment)
/src/db.ts                         - In-memory database and seed data
/src/middleware/logger.ts          - HTTP request logger middleware
/src/routes/posts.ts               - Posts CRUD routes (no auth)
/src/routes/comments.ts            - Comments CRUD routes (no auth)
/tests/auth.test.ts                - JWT auth tests (specifications)
/tests/posts.test.ts               - Basic posts endpoint tests
/tests/comments.test.ts            - Basic comments endpoint tests
```

---

This codebase is well-structured with clear separation of concerns. The test file (`auth.test.ts`) serves as a comprehensive specification for the JWT authentication system you need to implement. The main areas requiring implementation are:

1. Authentication middleware to verify JWT tokens
2. Auth routes for registration and login
3. Protection of write operations (POST, PUT, DELETE) for posts and comments
4. Ownership checks for modifications
5. Password hashing (to address the plaintext password issue)

